data.content:
Gdańsk University of Technology
The Gdańsk University of Technology is a higher education institution with a complex academic system, comprising various faculties and study programs. It has a detailed set of rules for student admission, confirmation of learning outcomes, and academic organization. The institution governs student registration and academic policies, overseeing diploma thesis procedures, and student conduct and participation. 

The university offers individual study programs and R&D teams, and provides financial assistance to students from funds allocated in the state budget, with detailed rules defined in the benefit rules. It also offers scholarships, prizes, and awards to students, with specific rules defined in the rector's regulation or dean's decision. 

In addition, the university has a specific procedure for granting financial assistance to students, with detailed rules for realization, as well as a rector's regulation on rules for charging tuition fees. The institution also has a procedure for transferring and recognizing learning outcomes when changing the field of study, faculty, and university, with a student register that outlines the detailed rules for student transfers and recognition of learning outcomes.

Gdańsk
Gdańsk is a city in Poland, hosting the Gdańsk University of Technology.<SEP>Gdańsk is the location where the university is situated.

Rector
The Rector is the highest authority at Gdańsk University of Technology, responsible for making academic and administrative decisions, including decisions regarding individual study programs, student conduct, scholarships, and financial prizes. They have the authority to remove students from the student register in certain circumstances, and serve as the superior of all university students, overseeing their academic and administrative matters.

Dean
The Dean is a university administrator responsible for various academic decisions and functions at Gdańsk University of Technology. As a high-ranking official, they oversee student conduct, making decisions regarding reinstatement of student rights when necessary. This includes having the authority to conduct an examination before a committee to aid in this process.

In their role, the Dean is responsible for a specific faculty, overseeing academic programs and schedules to ensure their smooth operation. They are also responsible for making decisions regarding diploma theses, examinations, individual study plans, and student admissions. Furthermore, the Dean has the authority to appoint tutors and make decisions on scholarships and recognition of learning outcomes.

In addition to these responsibilities, the Dean serves as the superior of all students at their faculty, with the authority to make decisions and provide guidance as needed. Overall, the Dean plays a crucial role in the academic life of students, ensuring their academic success and well-being.
